## Activate certificate

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Body example

```json
{
    "shop_id": "...",
    "shop_secret": "...",
    "owner_identifier": "owner phone number for personal certificates",
    "owner_name": "buyer phone number for personal certificates",
    "nominal": 1000 // For pools with flexible nominal
}
```

> Request example

```shell
curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --request PATCH \
  --data-binary "@data.json" \
  https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/:code/activate
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "payload": {
      "status": "active",
      "code": "...",
      "balance": 1000,
      "nominal": 1000,
      "personal": false,
      "activated_date": "...",
      "expiration_date": "...",
      "deactivated_date": "...",
      "expiration_days": 30,
      "certificate_pool_code": "...",
      "streams": ["..."],
      "min_order_value": 50,
      "payable_order_share": 90
    }
}
```

Activates inactive certificate.

### HTTP Request


`POST https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/:code/activate`
### Query Parameters

| Parameter        | Required | Description                                                         |
|------------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id          | true     | Your API key                                                        |
| shop_secret      | true     | Your API secret key                                                 |
| owner_identifier | false    | Owner's phone (identifier, required for personal certificates)      |
| owner_name       | false    | Owner's name (may be required for personal certificates)            |
| nominal          | false    | Overwrite certificate's nominal (for pools with a flexible nominal) |





